# Server crontab documentation (do not install automatically).
#
# Each line uses minute=`*`, so the job runs once per minute during the given
# hour (UTC or server-local, matching the live VPS crontab). Scripts must
# therefore be idempotent and use a shared flock to prevent overlap.
#
# Live schedule on /home/galois/bots/tldr_news:

# Every minute during hour 10: IMAP ingestion + generate --changed
* 10 * * * cd /home/galois/bots/tldr_news && ./automation.sh

# Every minute during hour 17: validate + commit + rebase/push
* 17 * * * cd /home/galois/bots/tldr_news && ./push_script.sh

# Every minute during hour 23: second ingestion window
* 23 * * * cd /home/galois/bots/tldr_news && ./automation.sh

# Every minute during hour 00: second push window
* 0 * * * cd /home/galois/bots/tldr_news && ./push_script.sh
